I’ve been going back & forth about sharing this because I’m such a private person when it comes to these things, but then I remember how seeing other women share their stories the past few months has helped me. My first #miscarriage was in October after 6 weeks. My second started a week ago today when our babies no longer had heartbeats at 10 weeks. Having two miscarriages in a row & losing 3 babies in less than six months is something I could never prepare myself for. The first loss was so painful, but this second loss is so much worse. We were so excited for our rainbow baby & couldn’t believe it happened so quickly. We had an early scan that showed two babies and a few seconds later the Dr told us it didnt seem like it would be a viable pregnancy & suspected it would end in miscarriage. Long story short it ended up being 5 weeks of weekly ultrasounds & tests full of so much uncertainty & unknowns. It is the most mentally, physically & spiritually exhausting thing I’ve ever gone through. 5 weeks of not knowing if my babies would be ok.. 5 weeks of my dr telling me to prepare myself for a miscarriage, but also not to give up hope because there are still two heartbeats. These last 6 weeks have been the most intense test of my faith, patience & strength. Although we were “prepared” for a miscarriage, nothing can really prepare you. This loss after 10 weeks feels so much harder in every way. I just wanted to share because over the last few months I’ve had friends on Instagram share about their miscarriages & it really helped me so much.. helped me feel stronger & less alone. So my hope is anyone reading this who is going through the same thing or has gone through the same thing might feel that. We only told a handful of people during both, but I don’t know how I would have gotten through it all without the support & guidance of two of my best friends who also had miscarriages, my mom who had two miscarriages before me, the support of our parents & my amazing husband. This is something that needs to be talked about more. Its one of the hardest things to go through & shouldn’t be kept secret for us to go through alone.. I am here always for anyone who needs it 🤍

social_posts.post_text: She back she back! Did my first castings last week & just landed in New York for a shoot! I’m so stoked to get back to work after having to take the last month & a half off. This job is actually really strenuous with so much travel, constantly trying to adjust to different time zones, long hours & days spent mostly on your feet. All of these things make it nearly impossible to do when you aren’t healthy. At first I took time off after learning my pregnancy was high risk to let my body rest & to give the babies a chance to grow/get healthy. I then had to cancel jobs/take more time off after getting covid & strep throat. Once I recovered from those  my pregnancy made me so sick I could barely eat or get off the couch which caused me to take more time off. The last & final stretch was the miscarriage & recovery forcing two more weeks off work. It felt like one thing after another with each week’s circumstances getting worse. I felt so much stress about having to take that much time off. It has felt like the longest & heaviest few weeks of my life, but has taught me so much. I learned the importance of rest & putting your health above all else. I learned to give myself proper time to heal without forcing myself back into work before I was ready. I learned money & work aren’t the most important things in life. I learned that God will always provide. I learned patience. I learned the importance of community. I learned I can’t always be in control. I learned to lean on others instead of trying to handle everything on my own. I learned to slow down. I also learned how much I love my job. I was able to enjoy some parts of my time off, but I am so happy to get back to a more normal life. Ready to work, ready leave the house, ready to get back to a healthier & lighter me. I want to thank you all for the love & support over the last few weeks, it’s meant more than you know. I am constantly in awe of how kind & loving people can be. I was supported by the closest people in my life, by people I haven’t seen or spoken to in years & by so many people I’ve never even met before. It has forever changed me & amidst everything that’s happened recently I feel so blessed & loved 🤍

Small things like a walk or a good stretch can do so much for your mind, body & mood. I always feel my best mentally and physically when I give myself daily movement. It feels surreal to finally be able to announce we’re having a baby! After 8 months of nonstop storms the sun is finally shining and we have our double rainbow. The sweetest ending to what felt like a series of incessant heartbreak. I am so amazed by how strong my body is and by how faithful God can be. After multiple miscarriages it can get hard to believe you’ll get your healthy baby.. I had days, weeks, and months of doubt. I experienced some of my darkest moments full of so much hopelessness and sadness. I would listen to “More than able” by Elevation Worship over and over and feel and repeat the lyrics “He’s not done with me yet. There’s so much more to the story, You’re not done with me yet, after this there will be Glory.” One day I had a switch and felt in my heart that there was more to our story than miscarriage.. after all the pain and heartache we would have our Glory, we’d just have to be patient.  It’s hard to express how much we love this little baby already.. we will cherish them forever and never forget what a gift this is. I want to say thank you from both of us to all of you. We have been so taken back by how much our community has covered us through this season. Friends, family, acquaintances and even people from the internet we’ve never met before..your love, prayers, messages, gifts & constant check ins have helped us heal and brought some much light into these past few months. We are just so grateful and can’t wait to finally meet our baby 🥺 for those of you still in the stormy part of your journey, I am with you, praying for you & sending all my love 🤍

We can’t wait to meet you little son 🤍

I finally changed my name after almost 8 years y’all!  I literally got everything done/switched exactly 4 weeks before my due date 😅 I was originally annoyed that I had to retake my picture again, but I actually love and think it’s so special that I’m pregnant with my little son in my new one and will cherish it forever 🥺🥲
**Also a heads up to anyone getting married.. the name you choose on your marriage license is the one you have to change it to unless you want to deal with Sacramento and stand before a judge in court to change it to anything else .. I now have two middle names because of the choices 23 year old me made loll I wish I knew before!
